Key Match Events: Mets scored 12 runs, with Pete Alonso hitting a three-run homer in the first inning and five more runs in the third inning.
Edwin Diaz pitched effectively in the eighth and ninth innings, securing the win.
Dodgers used Brent Honeywell Jr. as a mop-up pitcher after Jack Flaherty struggled.
Post-Match Reflections: Mets' players and manager expressed relief and excitement about the comeback victory.
The series now moves to Los Angeles, where the Mets face a more favorable matchup.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The series going back to Los Angeles for Game 6.
Dodgers' bullpen game setup for Game 6.
Andy Pages became the youngest Dodgers player to hit two home runs in a postseason game.
